 Port Elizabeth - Walmer detectives, in Port Elizabeth, are urgently trying to trace a 45-year-old Port Elizabeth man, who went missing from his home on Thursday. According to police information, on 4 December 2019, Kefas Marufu, a 45-year-old male from Zimbabwe, was taken to hospital by his brother as he is suffering from depression. "He was given medication and sent home. He slept at his brother’s home in Marikana in Walmer so that his brother could watch over him," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "On Thursday, he left his brother’s house to go to his home in Smallman Street, Walmer, to shower. "Several attempts to contact him on his cellphone failed and the family went to his house later that evening and found the front door open, but the security gate locked. The gate was forced open to gain entry." She sid that there were blankets and a shirt with blood. "All his medication packets were empty." At 01:00 on Friday morning, they reported the matter to the police. "Marufu is severely depressed and is in urgent need of help," Col Naidu said. "Anyone who may have seen him  or may know of his whereabouts is asked to contact Detective Warrant Officer Rudolf Baxter at SAPS Walmer on 082 442 0937 or SAPS Walmer  on 041 5098 4006 or Crime Stop 08600 10111 or their nearest police station." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 